{
  "texts": [
    "In the tests considered in Navarro et al. (2022), τ = 4dt yields stable simulations, while smaller (τ = 2dt) or much larger (τ = 64dt) values produce unstable solution similar to those demonstrated in Figure 6 from Navarro et al. (2022).",
    "It should also be noted that higher values of thermal conductivity may require a longer relaxation time to maintain a stable simulation.",
    "The factor f sat sets the saturation of the conductive heat flux, reducing its value for stability purposes.",
    "Following Fisher, Canfield, and McClymont (1985) and Meyer, Balsara, and Aslam (2012) the saturation factor is written as",
    "where c S = √ γp/ρ denotes the speed of sound and γ is the adiabatic index."
  ]
}